Added `pinentry-curses` to `home-manager/git/default.nix`:

```nix
  home.packages = with pkgs; [
    git
    git-lfs
    pinentry-curses # passphrase prompt for GPG-signing commits
  ];
```

This installs the package, which provides the curses-based passphrase prompt the GPG agent uses when signing commits (`signByDefault = true`, line 58).

One thing to be aware of: installing the package alone makes the binary available, but `gpg-agent` only uses it if it's told to via `pinentry-program` in `~/.gnupg/gpg-agent.conf`. If signing already works for you and you just needed the package present in the environment, you're done. If you want it wired up declaratively too, home-manager's `services.gpg-agent` can set it:

```nix
services.gpg-agent = {
  enable = true;
  pinentry.package = pkgs.pinentry-curses;
};
```

Want me to add that `gpg-agent` block as well, or leave it at just the package?

